<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1897-04-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1897-04-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="255" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d255">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Sherman</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">White</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1897-04-24"><hi rend="italic">April 24,
                                1897</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Our patrol fleet sails May 1. Sealing vessels returning with spring catch
                            will also put to sea about same time. Modus, to be effective, should be
                            agreed upon without delay. Explain situation and renew effort for answer
                            from British Government.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Sherman.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>